## [PROJECT — CUSTOMIZE]

### Page components are thin orchestrators

Pages live under **`webapp/src/pages/`** (e.g. `CanvasPage.jsx`). Their jobs are: compose hooks and store selectors, keep minimal local UI state, and render layout plus focused child components. Avoid stuffing large Konva/canvas logic, big style blocks, or one-off sub-UI inline—delegate to `webapp/src/components/`.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — page doing too much (inline canvas + AI + header logic)
export default function CanvasPage() { /* hundreds of lines */ }

// ✅ GOOD — page wires data + layout, children own UI domains
export default function CanvasPage() {
  return (
    <>
      <Header />
      <Canvas />
    </>
  );
}
```

### Sub-components do one thing

UI lives under **`webapp/src/components/`** with feature folders such as **`canvas/`** (stage, toolbar, shapes), **`ai/`**, **`auth/`**, **`design-system/`**, **`ui/`**, and shared **`icons/`**. Prefer small components (`Toolbar`, `ZoomControls`, `AIPanel`) over monoliths.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — one component owns canvas + AI + presence + zoom

// ✅ GOOD — focused pieces composed on the page or in Canvas
// webapp/src/components/canvas/Canvas.jsx orchestrates; shapes live in canvas/shapes/
```

### Co-location rule

Canvas-specific UI belongs under **`webapp/src/components/canvas/`** (and **`canvas/shapes/`** for `Rectangle`, `Circle`, `Text`). Auth screens use **`webapp/src/components/auth/`**. Shared primitives use **`webapp/src/components/design-system/`**. If something is only used from one page and is tiny, co-locating next to that page is optional; this repo mostly centralizes under `components/`.

### Conventions — data fetching and shared utils

#### Data — hooks, Zustand, and the AI HTTP client

Realtime canvas data flows through **Firebase (Firestore + Realtime DB)** using hooks under **`webapp/src/hooks/`** (e.g. `useAuth`, `useObjectSync`, `usePresenceSync`, `useCursorTracking`) and Zustand stores under **`webapp/src/stores/`** (`firestoreStore.js`, `localStore.js`, `presenceStore.js`, with **`webapp/src/stores/actions.js`** for cross-cutting mutations). UI components should use those hooks/stores—not ad hoc `fetch` to Firebase APIs.

The **AI agent** uses **`webapp/src/services/aiService.js`** (HTTP + SSE to the FastAPI backend). Only that service layer should call the agent API; components call `executeAICommandStream` / helpers exported there.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — subscription/sync hooks colocated under hooks/
useObjectSync(canvasId);
useAuth();

// ✅ GOOD — AI calls go through the service
import { executeAICommandStream } from "../services/aiService";
```

#### Helper functions — co-location vs shared utils

Duplication is fine until the **third** copy—then extract to **`webapp/src/utils/`** (e.g. `objectUtils.js`, `toast.js`) or, for design tokens, **`webapp/src/styles/tokens.js`**.

**Utils / libs in this repo:** `webapp/src/utils/objectUtils.js`, `webapp/src/utils/toast.js`, `webapp/src/lib/firebase.js`, `webapp/src/styles/tokens.js`.
